Subject: [PATCH 4/6] Expose `crow:pet-position` IPC hook for gateway-driven placement

Crow's `crow_wm_open` tool (to land in Phase 3.1) needs to tell the
pet-mode window where to sit relative to the Blockly kiosk — nominally
anchored to the right edge of the kiosk's host display, bottom-aligned
with a configurable margin. That's a gateway → Electron-main direction
of travel, so it has to cross an IPC boundary.

This patch adds a single `ipcMain.handle('crow:pet-position', ...)`
channel in `src/main/index.ts` that accepts `{ x, y, width, height }`
or a symbolic anchor (`'right' | 'left' | 'bottom-right' | ...`) and
calls into `WindowManager.setPetBounds()` (new method in
`window-manager.ts`). The renderer does not use this channel; only the
external Crow gateway writes to it via a small named-pipe / unix-socket
bridge that ships alongside the AppImage (bridge itself is Phase 3.1).

Applies against: vendor/open-llm-vtuber-web @ d176e7df2366952e3bacbf12cf9a8b18a4315932

